---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

import stepIndex from '../../data/watch-model-think/index.json';
import step1 from '../../data/watch-model-think/water_boils_at_a_temperature_of.json';
import step2 from '../../data/watch-model-think/this_is_definitely_not_a.json';
import step3 from '../../data/watch-model-think/the_big_red_ball_rolled_down_the.json';
import step4 from '../../data/watch-model-think/do_re_mi_fa_sol_la.json';
import loopChart from '../../data/watch-model-think/loop_chart.json';
import persistence from '../../data/watch-model-think/feature_persistence.json';
import calibration from '../../data/watch-model-think/calibration.json';
import interference from '../../data/watch-model-think/interference.json';

const frontmatter = {
  title: "Watch a Language Model Think",
  date: "2026-04-01",
  description: "I used sparse autoencoders to look inside GPT-2. I found interpretable concepts, feature loops, and a temperature feature that fires correctly while the model gets the answer wrong.",
  tags: ["interpretability", "SAE", "interactive"],
  thread: "interpretability",
  type: "experiment",
  project: "trust-bench",
  featured: true,
};

const formattedDate = new Date(frontmatter.date).toLocaleDateString('en-US', {
  year: 'numeric',
  month: 'long',
  day: 'numeric',
});
---

<Base title={`${frontmatter.title} | Amaljith Kuttamath`} description={frontmatter.description}>
  <article class="prose post-article animate-in">
    <header class="post-header">
      <div class="post-meta">
        <time class="mono post-date">{formattedDate}</time>
      </div>
      <h1>{frontmatter.title}</h1>
      <p class="post-description">{frontmatter.description}</p>
      <div class="post-tags">
        {frontmatter.tags.map((tag) => (
          <span class="tag">{tag}</span>
        ))}
      </div>
    </header>

    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "Article",
      "headline": frontmatter.title,
      "description": frontmatter.description,
      "datePublished": frontmatter.date,
      "dateModified": frontmatter.date,
      "author": {
        "@type": "Person",
        "name": "Amaljith Kuttamath",
        "url": "https://amaljithkuttamath.github.io"
      }
    })} />

    <p>GPT-2 has a feature that activates for temperature. It fires correctly on "Water boils at a temperature of." The model still outputs 1,000 degrees Fahrenheit.</p>

    <p>I used <a href="https://github.com/TransformerLensOrg/TransformerLens" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">TransformerLens</a> and <a href="https://github.com/jbloomAus/SAELens" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">SAELens</a> to extract sparse autoencoder features from GPT-2 small (124M parameters). I tested 18 prompts, scored them for feature interpretability and attribution coverage, and kept the four that produced the clearest findings. Click any generated token below to see what fired inside.</p>

    <div class="stepper-widget" role="region" aria-label="Interactive feature explorer">
      <div class="stepper-header">
        <span class="stepper-step-text" id="step-text"></span>
        <div class="stepper-dots" id="step-dots" role="navigation" aria-label="Step navigation"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="stepper-body" id="stepper-body">
        <div class="token-row" id="token-row"></div>
        <div class="feature-detail" id="feature-detail" aria-live="polite"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="stepper-callout" id="stepper-callout"></div>
      <div class="stepper-footer">
        <button class="stepper-prev" id="stepper-prev" style="visibility:hidden">← Back</button>
        <span class="stepper-hint" id="stepper-hint"></span>
        <button class="stepper-next" id="stepper-next">Next →</button>
      </div>
    </div>

    <script id="step-data" type="application/json" set:html={JSON.stringify([step1, step2, step3, step4])}></script>
    <script id="step-index-data" type="application/json" set:html={JSON.stringify(stepIndex)}></script>
    <script id="loop-chart-data" type="application/json" set:html={JSON.stringify(loopChart)}></script>
    <script id="persistence-data" type="application/json" set:html={JSON.stringify(persistence)}></script>
    <script id="calibration-data" type="application/json" set:html={JSON.stringify(calibration)}></script>

    <h2>Features persist across the sequence</h2>

    <p>When you click through Step 1 above, the temperature feature (#19375) fires on "about" and stays active through "degrees," "Fahrenheit," and "Celsius." It drops on structural tokens like parentheses and punctuation, then returns. The feature has a lifetime, not just a position.</p>

    <figure class="chart-container">
      <svg id="persistence-chart" role="img" aria-label="Chart showing temperature feature activation across 13 generated tokens"></svg>
      <figcaption>Activation of feature #19375 ("temperature in degrees F and C") across the generated sequence. The feature persists but drops on structural tokens.</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <p>This is what "circuit tracing" looks like at the simplest level. A concept activates in the residual stream and propagates forward, influencing multiple output tokens. The tools to trace these circuits exist (<a href="https://github.com/anthropics/attribution-graphs-frontend" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Anthropic open-sourced theirs</a>), but they only work on about 25% of prompts. For the rest, the circuits are too tangled to follow.</p>

    <h2>Feature loops explain repetition</h2>

    <p>Step 4 is the most interesting finding. When GPT-2 generates "vida de la vida de la vida de la..." from "Do re mi fa sol la," it is not random repetition. Four SAE features cycle in lockstep.</p>

    <figure class="chart-container">
      <svg id="loop-chart" role="img" aria-label="Chart showing four SAE features cycling in a repeating pattern"></svg>
      <figcaption>Four features take turns firing across three repetition cycles. Each feature fires on exactly one token in the pattern, then goes silent. Activations barely decay.</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <p>Feature #3900 ("Spanish la phrases") fires at 35.8, then 46.6, then 43.3. There is no internal signal telling the model to stop. Repetition in small language models is a feature loop with no exit condition. The SAE shows you the mechanism, not just the symptom.</p>

    <h2>Confidence and attribution disagree</h2>

    <p>The features say one thing. The model's confidence says another. When GPT-2 generates "hill" after "The big red ball rolled down the," the features push hard: 545% attribution coverage. But the model is only 6.4% confident. That gap is the signal.</p>

    <figure class="chart-container">
      <svg id="calibration-chart" role="img" aria-label="Scatter plot showing model confidence vs feature attribution coverage"></svg>
      <figcaption>Each dot is a generated token. X-axis: how confident the model was. Y-axis: how much the top features explain. When features push hard but confidence is low, other forces are pulling the output elsewhere.</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <p>High attribution coverage with low confidence means the features are pushing strongly, but other features (or the residual error term) are pushing back. The model is "deliberating." Low attribution coverage with high confidence means the model is sure, but the features you can see do not explain why. Both cases are problems for anyone trying to interpret model behavior.</p>

    <h2>What attention showed (and didn't)</h2>

    <p>Before SAE features, I tried raw attention. I exported SmolLM2-135M to ONNX with attention outputs, ran it in the browser at 7 tokens per second, and tested the same 18 prompts with an automated scoring system.</p>

    <p>None of the prompts produced readable attention patterns. Layer 0 attended to function words like "the" and "is." Deeper layers dumped 50-80% of attention on the first token position, a <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2309.17453" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">known artifact</a> in small transformers. Attention weights tell you where the model looks, not why it chose a particular output. This is why the interpretability community moved to sparse autoencoders.</p>

    <h2>What this means</h2>

    <p>Interpretability tools work. A temperature feature fires on temperature text. A negation feature fires on "not." These are real directions in the model's representation space, not post-hoc rationalizations.</p>

    <p>But seeing concepts is not understanding behavior. The temperature feature fires and the model still outputs the wrong temperature. Features compete in ways that are hard to predict. Superposition means every feature shares neurons with unrelated concepts. And when the model gets stuck, the features just cycle with no mechanism to break free.</p>

    <p>Neel Nanda, who created TransformerLens and leads mechanistic interpretability at Google DeepMind, <a href="https://80000hours.org/podcast/episodes/neel-nanda-mechanistic-interpretability/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">put it this way</a>: the most ambitious vision of mechanistic interpretability is probably dead. What remains is useful but partial. Picking up 90% of the concepts 90% of the time helps, as long as we pair it with other techniques.</p>

    <p>For practitioners: these tools are better at explaining failures than verifying correctness. If your model does something wrong, features can tell you why. If your model does something right, they cannot promise it will keep being right.</p>

    <h2>Reproduce this</h2>

    <pre><code>{`import transformer_lens as tl
from sae_lens import SAE

model = tl.HookedTransformer.from_pretrained("gpt2-small")
sae, cfg, sparsity = SAE.from_pretrained(
    release="gpt2-small-res-jb",
    sae_id="blocks.8.hook_resid_pre",
)

prompt = "Water boils at a temperature of"
logits, cache = model.run_with_cache(prompt)
residual = cache["blocks.8.hook_resid_pre"]
feature_acts = sae.encode(residual)

top_features = feature_acts[0, -1].topk(10)
for val, idx in zip(top_features.values, top_features.indices):
    print(f"Feature #{idx.item()}: activation {val.item():.1f}")`}</code></pre>
  </article>
</Base>

<script is:inline>
(function() {
  var steps = JSON.parse(document.getElementById('step-data').textContent);
  var stepIndex = JSON.parse(document.getElementById('step-index-data').textContent);
  var loopData = JSON.parse(document.getElementById('loop-chart-data').textContent);
  var persistData = JSON.parse(document.getElementById('persistence-data').textContent);
  var calData = JSON.parse(document.getElementById('calibration-data').textContent);

  var currentStep = 0;
  var selectedTokenIdx = -1;
  var genSpanMap = [];

  var stepText = document.getElementById('step-text');
  var stepDots = document.getElementById('step-dots');
  var tokenRow = document.getElementById('token-row');
  var featureDetail = document.getElementById('feature-detail');
  var calloutEl = document.getElementById('stepper-callout');
  var hint = document.getElementById('stepper-hint');
  var nextBtn = document.getElementById('stepper-next');
  var prevBtn = document.getElementById('stepper-prev');

  for (var i = 0; i < steps.length; i++) {
    var dot = document.createElement('span');
    dot.className = 'dot';
    dot.setAttribute('data-step', i);
    dot.setAttribute('tabindex', '0');
    dot.setAttribute('role', 'button');
    dot.setAttribute('aria-label', 'Go to step ' + (i + 1));
    dot.style.cursor = 'pointer';
    dot.addEventListener('click', function() {
      currentStep = parseInt(this.getAttribute('data-step'));
      renderStep();
    });
    stepDots.appendChild(dot);
  }

  function renderStep() {
    var data = steps[currentStep];
    var meta = stepIndex[currentStep];
    selectedTokenIdx = -1;
    genSpanMap = [];
    stepText.textContent = 'Step ' + (currentStep + 1) + ' of ' + steps.length + ': ' + meta.title;
    var dots = stepDots.querySelectorAll('.dot');
    for (var i = 0; i < dots.length; i++) {
      dots[i].className = 'dot';
      if (i === currentStep) dots[i].className = 'dot active';
      if (i < currentStep) dots[i].className = 'dot done';
    }
    tokenRow.innerHTML = '';
    var inputTokens = data.input_tokens || data.prompt.split(' ');
    for (var i = 0; i < inputTokens.length; i++) {
      var span = document.createElement('span');
      span.className = 'token token-input';
      span.textContent = inputTokens[i].trim() || inputTokens[i];
      tokenRow.appendChild(span);
    }
    var sep = document.createElement('span');
    sep.className = 'token-sep';
    sep.textContent = '\u2192';
    tokenRow.appendChild(sep);
    // Compute max logit_attr across all generated tokens for intensity scaling
    var maxLogitAttr = 1;
    for (var j = 0; j < data.generated_tokens.length; j++) {
      var feats = data.generated_tokens[j].features;
      if (feats && feats.length > 0) {
        var topAttr = Math.abs(feats[0].logit_attr);
        if (topAttr > maxLogitAttr) maxLogitAttr = topAttr;
      }
    }

    for (var j = 0; j < data.generated_tokens.length; j++) {
      var tokenText = data.generated_tokens[j].token.trim();
      if (!tokenText) continue;
      var span = document.createElement('span');
      span.className = 'token token-generated';
      span.textContent = tokenText;

      // Color intensity based on top feature's logit attribution
      var feats = data.generated_tokens[j].features;
      if (feats && feats.length > 0) {
        var intensity = Math.abs(feats[0].logit_attr) / maxLogitAttr;
        var bgAlpha = 0.04 + intensity * 0.18;
        span.style.background = 'color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-color) ' + Math.round(bgAlpha * 100) + '%, transparent)';
        span.style.borderColor = 'color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-color) ' + Math.round((0.1 + intensity * 0.3) * 100) + '%, transparent)';
      }
      span.setAttribute('data-idx', j);
      span.setAttribute('tabindex', '0');
      span.setAttribute('role', 'button');
      span.setAttribute('aria-label', 'Inspect features for: ' + tokenText);
      span.addEventListener('click', function() { selectToken(parseInt(this.getAttribute('data-idx'))); });
      span.addEventListener('keydown', function(e) { if (e.key === 'Enter' || e.key === ' ') { e.preventDefault(); selectToken(parseInt(this.getAttribute('data-idx'))); } });
      tokenRow.appendChild(span);
      genSpanMap.push({ el: span, idx: j });
    }
    if (data.callout) { calloutEl.innerHTML = '<strong>Notice:</strong> ' + esc(data.callout); calloutEl.style.display = 'block'; }
    else { calloutEl.style.display = 'none'; }
    hint.textContent = 'Click a generated token to see what features drove it.';
    prevBtn.style.visibility = currentStep === 0 ? 'hidden' : 'visible';
    nextBtn.textContent = currentStep === steps.length - 1 ? 'Done' : 'Next \u2192';
    featureDetail.innerHTML = ''; featureDetail.style.display = 'none';
    if (genSpanMap.length > 0) selectToken(genSpanMap[0].idx);
  }

  function selectToken(idx) {
    selectedTokenIdx = idx;
    var data = steps[currentStep];
    var tokenData = data.generated_tokens[idx];
    genSpanMap.forEach(function(item) { item.el.classList.toggle('selected', item.idx === idx); });
    if (!tokenData) { featureDetail.style.display = 'none'; return; }
    featureDetail.style.display = 'block';
    var features = tokenData.features.filter(function(f) { return f.label && f.label !== 'unlabeled feature'; }).slice(0, 5);
    if (features.length === 0) features = tokenData.features.slice(0, 5);
    var maxAttr = Math.max.apply(null, features.map(function(f) { return Math.abs(f.logit_attr); }));
    var html = '<div class="fd-header">Features for <span class="fd-accent">' + esc(tokenData.token.trim()) + '</span></div>';
    for (var i = 0; i < features.length; i++) {
      var f = features[i];
      var w = maxAttr > 0 ? (Math.abs(f.logit_attr) / maxAttr) * 100 : 0;
      var sign = f.logit_attr >= 0 ? '+' : '';
      html += '<div class="fd-row"><span class="fd-label">' + esc(f.label) + '</span><span class="fd-val">' + sign + f.logit_attr.toFixed(1) + '</span><div class="fd-bar-track"><div class="fd-bar" style="width:' + w + '%;' + (f.logit_attr < 0 ? 'background:var(--fg-muted);' : '') + '"></div></div></div>';
    }
    var preds = tokenData.predictions.slice(0, 3);
    html += '<div class="fd-preds">';
    for (var i = 0; i < preds.length; i++) {
      var p = preds[i];
      html += '<span class="fd-pill' + (p.chosen ? ' fd-chosen' : '') + '">' + esc(p.token.trim() || p.token) + ' ' + (p.prob * 100).toFixed(1) + '%</span>';
    }
    html += '</div>';
    featureDetail.innerHTML = html;
  }

  function esc(str) { var d = document.createElement('div'); d.appendChild(document.createTextNode(str)); return d.innerHTML; }

  nextBtn.addEventListener('click', function() {
    if (currentStep < steps.length - 1) { currentStep++; renderStep(); }
    else {
      // Scroll to next section after the widget
      var widget = document.querySelector('.stepper-widget');
      var next = widget.nextElementSibling;
      while (next && next.tagName === 'SCRIPT') next = next.nextElementSibling;
      if (next) next.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth' });
    }
  });
  prevBtn.addEventListener('click', function() {
    if (currentStep > 0) { currentStep--; renderStep(); }
  });

  renderStep();

  // ── Charts ──────────────────────────────────────

  function svgEl(tag, attrs) {
    var el = document.createElementNS('http://www.w3.org/2000/svg', tag);
    if (attrs) for (var k in attrs) el.setAttribute(k, attrs[k]);
    return el;
  }

  function drawBarChart(svgId, tokens, values, label, color) {
    var svg = document.getElementById(svgId);
    if (!svg) return;
    svg.innerHTML = '';
    var container = svg.parentElement;
    var width = container.clientWidth - 32;
    var height = 180;
    var pad = { top: 15, right: 15, bottom: 45, left: 40 };
    var plotW = width - pad.left - pad.right;
    var plotH = height - pad.top - pad.bottom;
    svg.setAttribute('width', width);
    svg.setAttribute('height', height);
    svg.setAttribute('viewBox', '0 0 ' + width + ' ' + height);

    var maxVal = Math.max.apply(null, values);
    maxVal = Math.ceil(maxVal / 10) * 10 || 10;
    var barW = Math.min(plotW / tokens.length - 2, 30);
    var gap = (plotW - barW * tokens.length) / (tokens.length + 1);

    // Y gridlines
    for (var v = 0; v <= maxVal; v += 10) {
      var y = pad.top + plotH - (v / maxVal) * plotH;
      svg.appendChild(svgEl('line', { x1: pad.left, x2: width - pad.right, y1: y, y2: y, stroke: 'rgba(255,255,255,0.06)', 'stroke-width': 1 }));
      var txt = svgEl('text', { x: pad.left - 6, y: y + 3, 'text-anchor': 'end', fill: '#7a7570', 'font-family': "'JetBrains Mono',monospace", 'font-size': '9px' });
      txt.textContent = v; svg.appendChild(txt);
    }

    // Bars
    for (var i = 0; i < tokens.length; i++) {
      var x = pad.left + gap + i * (barW + gap);
      var barH = values[i] > 0 ? (values[i] / maxVal) * plotH : 0;
      var y = pad.top + plotH - barH;
      var opacity = values[i] > 0 ? 0.7 : 0.1;
      svg.appendChild(svgEl('rect', { x: x, y: y, width: barW, height: barH, rx: 2, fill: color, opacity: opacity }));
      var lbl = svgEl('text', { x: x + barW / 2, y: height - 8, 'text-anchor': 'middle', fill: '#7a7570', 'font-family': "'JetBrains Mono',monospace", 'font-size': '8px', transform: 'rotate(-30,' + (x + barW / 2) + ',' + (height - 8) + ')' });
      lbl.textContent = tokens[i].trim(); svg.appendChild(lbl);
    }
  }

  function drawLoopChart() {
    var svg = document.getElementById('loop-chart');
    if (!svg) return;
    svg.innerHTML = '';
    var container = svg.parentElement;
    var width = container.clientWidth - 32;
    var height = 220;
    var pad = { top: 20, right: 20, bottom: 40, left: 45 };
    var plotW = width - pad.left - pad.right;
    var plotH = height - pad.top - pad.bottom;
    svg.setAttribute('width', width);
    svg.setAttribute('height', height);
    svg.setAttribute('viewBox', '0 0 ' + width + ' ' + height);

    var maxAct = 0;
    for (var fi = 0; fi < loopData.features.length; fi++)
      for (var ti = 0; ti < loopData.features[fi].activations.length; ti++)
        if (loopData.features[fi].activations[ti] > maxAct) maxAct = loopData.features[fi].activations[ti];
    maxAct = Math.ceil(maxAct / 10) * 10;
    var nTokens = loopData.tokens.length;
    var xStep = plotW / (nTokens - 1);
    var colors = [getComputedStyle(document.documentElement).getPropertyValue('--accent-color').trim() || '#5fb88a', '#c2a04f', '#7a8fb8', '#b87a9f'];

    for (var v = 0; v <= maxAct; v += 10) {
      var y = pad.top + plotH - (v / maxAct) * plotH;
      svg.appendChild(svgEl('line', { x1: pad.left, x2: width - pad.right, y1: y, y2: y, stroke: 'rgba(255,255,255,0.06)', 'stroke-width': 1 }));
      var lbl = svgEl('text', { x: pad.left - 8, y: y + 3, 'text-anchor': 'end', fill: '#7a7570', 'font-family': "'JetBrains Mono',monospace", 'font-size': '9px' });
      lbl.textContent = v; svg.appendChild(lbl);
    }
    for (var ti = 0; ti < nTokens; ti++) {
      var x = pad.left + ti * xStep;
      var lbl = svgEl('text', { x: x, y: height - 8, 'text-anchor': 'middle', fill: '#7a7570', 'font-family': "'JetBrains Mono',monospace", 'font-size': '9px' });
      lbl.textContent = loopData.tokens[ti].trim(); svg.appendChild(lbl);
    }
    for (var ci = 1; ci < 3; ci++) {
      var cx = pad.left + (ci * 4 - 0.5) * xStep;
      svg.appendChild(svgEl('line', { x1: cx, x2: cx, y1: pad.top, y2: pad.top + plotH, stroke: 'rgba(255,255,255,0.1)', 'stroke-width': 1, 'stroke-dasharray': '4,4' }));
    }
    for (var fi = 0; fi < loopData.features.length; fi++) {
      var feat = loopData.features[fi];
      var color = colors[fi % colors.length];
      var pts = [];
      for (var ti = 0; ti < feat.activations.length; ti++) {
        var x = pad.left + ti * xStep;
        var y = pad.top + plotH - (feat.activations[ti] / maxAct) * plotH;
        pts.push(x + ',' + y);
        if (feat.activations[ti] > 0) {
          var c = svgEl('circle', { cx: x, cy: y, r: 4, fill: color });
          var title = svgEl('title'); title.textContent = feat.label + ': ' + feat.activations[ti]; c.appendChild(title);
          svg.appendChild(c);
        }
      }
      svg.appendChild(svgEl('polyline', { points: pts.join(' '), fill: 'none', stroke: color, 'stroke-width': 1.5, opacity: 0.6 }));
    }
    var legendY = pad.top + 2;
    for (var fi = 0; fi < loopData.features.length; fi++) {
      var feat = loopData.features[fi];
      var color = colors[fi % colors.length];
      svg.appendChild(svgEl('rect', { x: pad.left + 4, y: legendY + fi * 14 - 4, width: 8, height: 8, rx: 2, fill: color }));
      var txt = svgEl('text', { x: pad.left + 16, y: legendY + fi * 14 + 3, fill: '#7a7570', 'font-family': "'JetBrains Mono',monospace", 'font-size': '8px' });
      txt.textContent = feat.label; svg.appendChild(txt);
    }
  }

  function drawCalibrationChart() {
    var svg = document.getElementById('calibration-chart');
    if (!svg) return;
    svg.innerHTML = '';
    var container = svg.parentElement;
    var width = container.clientWidth - 32;
    var height = 240;
    var pad = { top: 20, right: 20, bottom: 35, left: 50 };
    var plotW = width - pad.left - pad.right;
    var plotH = height - pad.top - pad.bottom;
    svg.setAttribute('width', width);
    svg.setAttribute('height', height);
    svg.setAttribute('viewBox', '0 0 ' + width + ' ' + height);

    var maxConf = 0.6;
    var maxCov = 6;

    // Grid
    for (var v = 0; v <= maxConf; v += 0.1) {
      var x = pad.left + (v / maxConf) * plotW;
      svg.appendChild(svgEl('line', { x1: x, x2: x, y1: pad.top, y2: pad.top + plotH, stroke: 'rgba(255,255,255,0.04)', 'stroke-width': 1 }));
      var lbl = svgEl('text', { x: x, y: height - 8, 'text-anchor': 'middle', fill: '#7a7570', 'font-family': "'JetBrains Mono',monospace", 'font-size': '9px' });
      lbl.textContent = Math.round(v * 100) + '%'; svg.appendChild(lbl);
    }
    for (var v = 0; v <= maxCov; v += 1) {
      var y = pad.top + plotH - (v / maxCov) * plotH;
      svg.appendChild(svgEl('line', { x1: pad.left, x2: width - pad.right, y1: y, y2: y, stroke: 'rgba(255,255,255,0.04)', 'stroke-width': 1 }));
      var lbl = svgEl('text', { x: pad.left - 6, y: y + 3, 'text-anchor': 'end', fill: '#7a7570', 'font-family': "'JetBrains Mono',monospace", 'font-size': '9px' });
      lbl.textContent = (v * 100) + '%'; svg.appendChild(lbl);
    }

    // Axis labels
    var xLabel = svgEl('text', { x: pad.left + plotW / 2, y: height - 1, 'text-anchor': 'middle', fill: '#7a7570', 'font-family': "'JetBrains Mono',monospace", 'font-size': '9px' });
    xLabel.textContent = 'model confidence'; svg.appendChild(xLabel);
    var yLabel = svgEl('text', { x: 10, y: pad.top + plotH / 2, 'text-anchor': 'middle', fill: '#7a7570', 'font-family': "'JetBrains Mono',monospace", 'font-size': '9px', transform: 'rotate(-90,10,' + (pad.top + plotH / 2) + ')' });
    yLabel.textContent = 'feature attribution'; svg.appendChild(yLabel);

    var promptColors = [getComputedStyle(document.documentElement).getPropertyValue('--accent-color').trim() || '#5fb88a', '#c2a04f', '#7a8fb8', '#b87a9f'];
    for (var pi = 0; pi < calData.length; pi++) {
      var p = calData[pi];
      var color = promptColors[pi % promptColors.length];
      for (var ti = 0; ti < p.tokens.length; ti++) {
        var t = p.tokens[ti];
        var cx = pad.left + Math.min(t.confidence / maxConf, 1) * plotW;
        var cy = pad.top + plotH - Math.min(t.attribution_coverage / maxCov, 1) * plotH;
        var dot = svgEl('circle', { cx: cx, cy: cy, r: 4, fill: color, opacity: 0.7 });
        var title = svgEl('title');
        title.textContent = '"' + t.token.trim() + '" conf=' + (t.confidence * 100).toFixed(1) + '% attr=' + (t.attribution_coverage * 100).toFixed(0) + '%';
        dot.appendChild(title);
        svg.appendChild(dot);
      }
    }

    // Legend
    for (var pi = 0; pi < calData.length; pi++) {
      var color = promptColors[pi % promptColors.length];
      var lx = pad.left + plotW - 180;
      var ly = pad.top + 8 + pi * 14;
      svg.appendChild(svgEl('circle', { cx: lx, cy: ly, r: 3, fill: color }));
      var short = calData[pi].prompt.length > 25 ? calData[pi].prompt.substring(0, 24) + '..' : calData[pi].prompt;
      var txt = svgEl('text', { x: lx + 8, y: ly + 3, fill: '#7a7570', 'font-family': "'JetBrains Mono',monospace", 'font-size': '8px' });
      txt.textContent = short; svg.appendChild(txt);
    }
  }

  // Draw persistence chart
  drawBarChart('persistence-chart', persistData.tokens, persistData.activations, persistData.label, getComputedStyle(document.documentElement).getPropertyValue('--accent-color').trim() || '#5fb88a');
  drawLoopChart();
  drawCalibrationChart();

  window.addEventListener('resize', function() {
    clearTimeout(window._chartResize);
    window._chartResize = setTimeout(function() {
      drawBarChart('persistence-chart', persistData.tokens, persistData.activations, persistData.label, getComputedStyle(document.documentElement).getPropertyValue('--accent-color').trim() || '#5fb88a');
      drawLoopChart();
      drawCalibrationChart();
    }, 200);
  });
})();
</script>

